parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Loss of Power

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Malfunctions of advanced safety features, such as emergency braking and lane departure warning systems, can increase the risk of accidents and compromise the safety of the driver and passengers.

which can cause confusion and distraction while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Missing or improperly installed interior components can pose a safety risk to the driver and passengers, including the risk of fire or electrocution.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Malfunctions of the infotainment system can cause inconvenience and distraction while driving, and may compromise the safety of the driver and passengers.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Power Loss and Limp Mode
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of engine power and activation of limp mode can cause the vehicle to slow down unexpectedly, increasing the risk of accidents or rear-ending.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent loss of engine power can cause the vehicle to struggle to accelerate, leading to hazardous situations, especially when merging or crossing intersections.
